OL,3,CFortnum apologises after Paralympians
OL,4,Cnot invited to party after meeting King
OL,6,F"For me yesterday being under the same
OL,7,Froof as the King and all the Olympic
OL,8,Fand Paralympic medallists and in one
OL,9,Fplace, but the Paralympic medallists
OL,10,Fhave to get in the car and drive home
OL,11,Fwhile the Olympic medallists get to
OL,12,Fenjoy a four-hour after-party with
OL,13,Fchampagne bottles with their name
OL,14,Fengraved into it. It's just unfair."
OL,16,FAccording to a screenshot posted by Mr
OL,17,FShaw on Instagram, a spokesperson for
OL,18,FFortnum & Mason apologised and said
OL,19,Fthere is a separate event for
OL,20,FParalympians "in the works".
